name: WASP-105
scenarioDescription:
The WASP-105 Exoplanetary System


Overview

WASP-105 is a star with 0.89 times the mass of the Sun, and 0.9 times its radius. It is located 823.6091312 light years away from the solar system.

WASP-105 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the WASP-105 system

WASP-105 b

WASP-105 b was discovered by the SuperWASP-South observatory using the Transit method. The mass of WASP-105 b is 572.094 times the mass of Earth. The radius of WASP-105 b is 10.761 that of Earth. At more than 10 Earth masses, WASP-105 b is an ice giant, a planet that is made up mostly of volatiles like water, amonia and methane, and enveloped by a dense hydrogen and helium atmosphere, much like Uranus and Neptune in our solar system. At more than 50 Earth masses, WASP-105 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
description: 3D visualisation and gravity simulation of the exoplanet system WASP-105, which contains 1 planets and was discovered by SuperWASP-South.
